    "summary": "International Reconstruction, Project Management, Procurement:\nEmployed in private sector in the Global Support Services as a Project Manager. Prior positions included Procurement Officer at the United Nations Secretariat (Headquarters), Procurement Division, Corporate & IT Procurement Section in New York City. Prior to the United Nations was a mobilized U.S Army Reservist as a lead Project Manager on a 40 acre $200M construction project in Afghanistan and Facility Manager for a $60M facility.  Expert knowledge of the entire transactional \u201clife cycle\u201d process of procurement to include; acquisition plan, statement of work, solicitation document annexes, issuance of \u201crequest for proposals,\u201d scoring (technical and commercial), notification of award, presentation to governing council and contract negotiation.\n         \nCorporate Real Estate, Project Management and Strategic Portfolio Management: \nSelected by General Motor\u2019s corporate real estate management to establish and operate an internal lease administration portfolio for one of its subsidiaries resulting in a highly successful operation. Corporate Real Estate portfolio consisted of over 450 real estate locations with $60M+  in annual lease payments.  Expert knowledge of the entire \u201clife cycle\u201d of a real estate project including; Acquisition, Management, Disposition and Facilities Management. Highly experienced in determining the value of a site, exceptional ability to develop acquisition financing, \u201chands on\u201d experience managing the relationships with the  A/E, CM, GC and all ad hoc consultants needed to develop the site, exceptional networking experience liaising  with brokers for sales and  thorough knowledge of property management. \n\n\nSpecialties: See above Professional Experience & Goals",
